SIMPLE: manager
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manager
<hw>Man"a*ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
manages; a conductor or director; <as>as, the <ex>manager</ex> of a
theater</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A skillful <qex>manager</qex> of the rabble.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who conducts business or household affairs
with economy and frugality; a good economist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A prince of great aspiring thoughts; in the main, a
<qex>manager</qex> of his treasure.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Temple.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A contriver; an intriguer.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>manageress</ent>⟦br⟧
